"5:103:19" : {s: 5, a: 103, w: 19, r: "كثر", t: "وَأَكْثَرُهُمْ", l: "أَكْثَر", lc: 80, tl: "wa-aktharuhum", lb: "অনেক বেশি, সবচেয়ে বেশি",e: "and most of them", b: "তাদের অধিকাংশই", i: "dan kebanyakan mereka", f: 4, rm: "To surpass in number or quantity, increase, multiply, happen often, copious, richness; To be much, many, numerous, a man whose ancestors are many or whose good deeds are many. A man possessing much good, river in paradise from which other rivers flow, talkative person.", ag: "واو الحال وأسم مرفوع وضمير متصل ", eg: "Circumstantial wa and Noun Nominative case and Pronoun suffix ", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "NOM", qual: "", deg: "", gen: "M", num: "S", mood: "", lu: "كَثُرَ،كَثِيرٌۭ،كَثِيرَةٌۭ،تَسْتَكْثِرُ"},
